[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Frontend Setup[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe frontend is served directly by Django. Open your browser and navigate to:[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mhttp://127.0.0.1:8000[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Algorithm Explanation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe priority scoring algorithm uses a weighted approach with four components:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 1. Urgency (40% default)[m
[32m+[m[32mBased on due date proximity:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Overdue: 1.0[m
[32m+[m[32m- Due today: 0.9[m
[32m+[m[32m- Tomorrow: 0.8[m
[32m+[m[32m- 2-3 days: 0.6[m
[32m+[m[32m- 4-7 days: 0.4[m
[32m+[m[32m- More than 7 days: 0.2[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2. Importance (30% default)[m
[32m+[m[32mNormalized user rating (1-10 scale to 0-1)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 3. Effort (20% default)[m
[32m+[m[32mInverse relationship with estimated hours:[m
[32m+[m[32m- 1 hour or less: 1.0[m
[32m+[m[32m- 1-4 hours: 0.7[m
[32m+[m[32m- 4-8 hours: 0.4[m
[32m+[m[32m- More than 8 hours: 0.2[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 4. Dependencies (10% default)[m
[32m+[m[32mTasks blocking others get higher priority[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Available Strategies[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Smart Balance: Balanced weighting of all factors[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fastest Wins: Emphasizes low-effort tasks (50% weight)[m
[32m+[m[32m- High Impact: Focuses on importance (60% weight)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Deadline Driven: Prioritizes urgency (70% weight)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## API Endpoints[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- POST /api/tasks/analyze/ - Analyze and sort tasks by priority[m
[32m+[m[32m- POST /api/tasks/suggest/ - Get top 3 task recommendations[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### API Behavior Note[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe APIs return "405 Method Not Allowed" for GET requests - this is expected and correct behavior. The endpoints are designed to only accept POST requests with task data.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### Correct Usage:[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m# POST requests work (expected)[m
[32m+[m[32mcurl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tasks/analyze/ \[m
[32m+[m[32m  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \[m
[32m+[m[32m  -d '[{"title": "Test", "due_date": "2024-12-15", "estimated_hours": 3, "importance": 8, "dependencies": []}]'[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# GET requests fail (expected - this is correct)[m
[32m+[m[32mcurl -X GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tasks/analyze/[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Design Decisions[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Algorithm Design[m
[32m+[m[32m- Weighted Sum Approach: Chosen for transparency and configurability[m
[32m+[m[32m- Normalized Scores: All components scaled to 0-1 for consistency[m
[32m+[m[32m- Strategy Pattern: Different weighting strategies for flexibility[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Frontend Architecture[m
[32m+[m[32m- Progressive Enhancement: Works even if backend is unavailable[m
[32m+[m[32m- Local Storage: Data persistence without server dependency[m
[32m+[m[32m- Responsive Design: Mobile-first approach with CSS Grid/Flexbox[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Error Handling[m
[32m+[m[32m- Graceful Degradation: Falls back to local analysis if API fails[m
[32m+[m[32m- User Feedback: Clear error messages and loading states[m
[32m+[m[32m- Input Validation: Client-side validation with helpful messages[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Time Breakdown[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Algorithm Design & Backend: 2 hours[m
[32m+[m[32m- Frontend Development: 1.5 hours[m
[32m+[m[32m- Testing & Debugging: 1 hour[m
[32m+[m[32m- Documentation: 0.5 hour[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Core Requirements Met[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Backend (Python/Django)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Task model with all required fields[m
[32m+[m[32m- Priority scoring algorithm with 4 factors[m
[32m+[m[32m- API endpoints for analysis and suggestions[m
[32m+[m[32m- Circular dependency detection[m
[32m+[m[32m- Error handling and validation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Frontend (HTML/CSS/JavaScript)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Task input form with validation[m
[32m+[m[32m- JSON bulk import[m
[32m+[m[32m- Strategy selection (4 options)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Priority visualization with color coding[m
[32m+[m[32m- Responsive design[m
[32m+[m[32m- Error handling and loading states[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Testing Guide[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Core Functionality Tests[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### Test 1: Basic Task Management[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Add a single task using the form[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Load sample tasks using the "Load Sample Tasks" button[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Analyze tasks using the "Analyze Tasks" button[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Verify tasks are sorted by priority score with color coding[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### Test 2: Strategy Switching[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Test different strategies (Smart Balance, Fastest Wins, High Impact, Deadline Driven)[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Verify each strategy produces different priority rankings[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Confirm strategy changes are reflected in the analysis[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### Test 3: API Testing[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Test POST /api/tasks/analyze/ with valid task data[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Test POST /api/tasks/suggest/ with valid task data[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Verify APIs return 200 status codes for valid requests[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Confirm APIs return appropriate error codes for invalid requests[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Edge Case Tests[m
[32m+[m[32m- Test form validation with invalid inputs[m
[32m+[m[32m- Test JSON parsing with invalid JSON[m
[32m+[m[32m- Test responsive design on different screen sizes[m
[32m+[m[32m- Test data persistence after browser refresh[m
